# iOS development workflow (GKP Radio)

## Default: Option C — EAS development build

When running or testing iOS, **always use the EAS development client workflow** unless the user explicitly asks for Simulator, local `expo run:ios`, or Expo Go.

App code is in `mobile/`. Do **not** suggest `cd mobile` when the shell is already in `mobile/`.

### Step 1 — Build dev client (when native code changed or first install)

```bash
npm run ios:dev
```

### Step 2 — Install on iPhone

Use the link/QR from [expo.dev](https://expo.dev) when the build finishes (internal distribution).

### Step 3 — Run JS against the dev client

```bash
npm run start:dev
```

Open the **GKP Radio** dev app on the phone (not Expo Go). Scan the Metro QR if needed.

## Other options (only when user asks)

| Option | When | Command |
|--------|------|---------|
| **C — EAS dev build** (default) | Real device, background audio, no local signing | `npm run ios:dev` then `npm run start:dev` |
| **A — Simulator** | Local Mac, no signing | `npm run ios:sim` |
| **B — Physical device** | Local Xcode install | `npm run ios:device` |
| **Expo Go + tunnel** | Quick UI only (no background audio) | `npm run start:tunnel` |

## Audio / background listening

- **Expo Go**: in-app only; background and lock screen **do not** work.
- **EAS dev client** (default): full `expo-audio` + lock screen on a **physical iPhone**.
- Never claim background audio works in Expo Go.

## App Store releases

Production iOS upload: `npm run appstore:ios` then `npm run appstore:ios:submit` (from `mobile/`).
